			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64176027"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64176027"><p>Hmm. That's possible, yes, but it would require that a statistically significant number of people A. have both ICE and electric powered vehicles, B. chose to use the ICE over the electric, and C. had the ICE fail to the point where they had to call for assistance to get it recorded.</p><p>I think that a more likely explanation is that EVs with LiFePo4 batteries (which includes some Tesla models) don't "hard fail" in cold weather until you're down to about -20C/-4F. They lose performance below 0C/32F, but there isn<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64176027">

</div>
